an have 4 toons at once.  I have at my access a lvl 65 warrior (280AA), and 65 Druid (270AA), and a 65 enchanter (326AA) and a lvl 65 enchanter (112AA).  How would you all PL this froggy??  Juggs in Seb?  Just curious from the people that have been around a long time and know the new zones.  Thank you in advance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alluriah>alluriah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/03 4:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need the smarts ;p  PL question....</span><hr size=1> Here is one idea that i have for you, subject to the following qualifiers:<br>
<br>
-  I have mostly tried this in plane of nightmares<br>
-  I only have access to 2 accounts (so i plevel my wizard with my enchanter), but it should work better with access to 3 accounts.  I will write it up as how i would do it if i had 2 enchanters to work with as well as my wizard.<br>
<br>
Step 1)  Have the wizard pull 2 mobs with snare, and have each enchanter charm one mob.  Have mobs Guard here.  Move enchanters back.  Tash before charm is optional, but helps will resists on the level 54 pillar and subsequent snares.  <br>
<br>
Step 2)  Have the wizard pull 2 more mobs with snare and have the enchanter set a charmed pet on each of them.  Wizard sit backs and meds at the edge of casting range.<br>
<br>
Step 3)  the mobs and the pets are usually do about the same damage to each other as none of them are hasted and slowed.  Wait a little bit of time with your enchanters ~20 seconds and then have them sit and Camp.  Have wizard standing and ready to go when they camp out.<br>
<br>
Step 4)  Enchanters camp out and this breaks charms / clears aggro.  All 4 mobs are mad at the wizard (remember snare) and are at ~20% life (depending on your timing).  Resnare, round up and quad normally.  Don't get too far out of range as they will regen alot (it's a feature).  If they get really low (below 10% before you break charm) sometimes they do not give experience (don't ask me why).  Remember to begin to relog in your other characters while quadding.<br>
<br>
Step 5)  Finish quad, check to see that you just got 2 blue bubbles of regular experience in 4 minutes and are at 80% mana, repeat.    <br>
<br>
Other thoughts:<br>
-Breaking charm normally (with invis) works the same (the enchanter get's no credit for the damage he does with his charmed pet if the pet is no longer charmed), but can be a hassle with aggro (mobs still mad at enchanter, split up, etc.) I found camping out the easiest thing to do and it did not slow me down.<br>
<br>
-  Substitue a druid for an enchanter and have the druid cast snare and pull (long lasting), give each mob a little click with your staff to establish a little bit of aggro.<br>
<br>
-  This method should work anywhere an enchanter can charm and fight non-summoning mobs and there is sufficient room, tier 2 and 3 exp should be insane.  Your wizard likely needs a few levels to take advantage of that however (resists).  <br>
 <br>
I'm interested to see what your results are and for all you retired enchanters / wizard wannabe's out there who are disgruntled with your ex-class, this is a great way to plevel another character class that is quite fun to play.  <br>
